1. An HTTP service that inspects the body of incoming POST/PUT requests for a forbidden substring loaded from a file at startup. Bodies that contain the substring are rejected with 403 and a "blocked" reason; bodies over a separately-configured maximum size are rejected with 413; everything else returns 200 with a confirmation. Every request is recorded as a JSONL audit line with method, path, status, body byte count, and timestamp. The blacklist substring and the size limit are both editable without recompiling the binary; cache: true means the operator restarts to pick up edits. Concurrency is fork-per-accept; audit log is fail-closed (on_error: abort).
